---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base
  title="Case Studies — Eidos AGI"
  description="Real systems running on contracts, not skills. No demos. No mockups. Actual production use."
>
    <article class="prose-page">
      <header class="page-hero">
        <h1>Case Studies</h1>
        <p class="subtitle">Real systems. Real contracts. No demos.</p>
      </header>

      <section class="content-section">
        <p>These aren't hypothetical examples. They're systems running in production — AI agents fulfilling contracts from git repos, with no skills files, no step-by-step instructions, and often no software at all.</p>
        <p>Each case study shows the contract, the data, what the AI produces, and why it works without being told how.</p>
      </section>

      <!-- Featured: Grocery -->
      <section class="content-section">
        <a href="/case-studies/grocery" class="cs-featured">
          <div class="cs-featured-media">
            <video autoplay loop muted playsinline>
              <source src="/videos/grocery-order.mp4" type="video/mp4" />
            </video>
            <div class="cs-featured-badge">Live</div>
          </div>
          <div class="cs-featured-content">
            <div class="cs-featured-label">Featured case study</div>
            <h2>Grocery ordering</h2>
            <p>A GitHub repo with YAML preferences and JSON Schema contracts. An AI reads them and orders groceries weekly. No code. No skills file. Just schemas and data.</p>
            <div class="cs-featured-stats">
              <div class="cs-stat">
                <span class="cs-stat-num">3</span>
                <span class="cs-stat-label">contracts</span>
              </div>
              <div class="cs-stat">
                <span class="cs-stat-num">5</span>
                <span class="cs-stat-label">preference files</span>
              </div>
              <div class="cs-stat">
                <span class="cs-stat-num">0</span>
                <span class="cs-stat-label">lines of code</span>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="cs-featured-stack">Perplexity Computer + GitHub + JSON Schema</div>
          </div>
        </a>
      </section>

      <!-- Coming soon -->
      <section class="content-section">
        <h2>Coming next</h2>
        <div class="cs-grid">
          <div class="cs-card">
            <div class="cs-card-number">01</div>
            <h3>Voice notes</h3>
            <p>A Mac app records voice, transcribes locally with Whisper, classifies via Claude Agent SDK, and stores in recording buckets that a search engine indexes.</p>
            <div class="cs-card-stats">
              <span>5 contracts</span>
              <span>3 languages</span>
              <span>3 processes</span>
            </div>
            <div class="cs-card-stack">Swift + Python + JSON Schema + Omni</div>
          </div>

          <div class="cs-card">
            <div class="cs-card-number">02</div>
            <h3>Project improvement</h3>
            <p>A forge scores any project across 10 dimensions, fixes the highest-impact gap, and records a snapshot. The snapshot schema is the contract.</p>
            <div class="cs-card-stats">
              <span>1 contract</span>
              <span>3 projects improved</span>
              <span>Self-improving</span>
            </div>
            <div class="cs-card-stack">improve-forge + JSON Schema</div>
          </div>

          <div class="cs-card">
            <div class="cs-card-number">03</div>
            <h3>Learning capture</h3>
            <p>A forge that extracts learnings from sessions, routes project-level fixes directly and proposes forge-level improvements to the overseer.</p>
            <div class="cs-card-stats">
              <span>1 contract</span>
              <span>15 learnings routed</span>
              <span>10 proposals</span>
            </div>
            <div class="cs-card-stack">learning-forge + forge-forge governance</div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="content-section">
        <div class="cs-cta">
          <p>The pattern is the same in every case. Define what you want as a schema. Give the AI the schema and the data. Let it figure out how.</p>
          <a href="/contract-driven-development" class="cs-cta-link">Read the argument: Contracts, Not Skills</a>
        </div>
      </section>

      <div class="related">
        <span class="related-label">Related</span>
        <div class="related-links">
          <a href="/contract-driven-development">Contracts, Not Skills</a>
          <a href="/forges">Forges</a>
          <a href="/trilogy">The Trilogy</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </article>
</Base>

<style is:global>
  /* Featured card */
  .cs-featured {
    display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 0;
    background: var(--color-surface); border-radius: var(--radius-md); overflow: hidden;
    text-decoration: none; transition: transform 0.2s ease;
    border: var(--border-width) solid color-mix(in srgb, var(--color-command) 25%, transparent);
  }
  .cs-featured:hover { transform: translateY(-3px); }
  .cs-featured-media { position: relative; }
  .cs-featured-media video { width: 100%; height: 100%; object-fit: cover; display: block; }
  .cs-featured-badge {
    position: absolute; top: var(--space-3); left: var(--space-3);
    font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: var(--text-xs);
    color: var(--color-command);
    background: color-mix(in srgb, var(--color-bg) 85%, transparent);
    backdrop-filter: blur(4px);
    padding: 2px 10px; border-radius: 3px;
  }
  .cs-featured-content { padding: var(--space-8); display: flex; flex-direction: column; justify-content: center; }
  .cs-featured-label { font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: var(--text-xs); color: var(--color-command); text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.1em; margin-bottom: var(--space-3); }
  .cs-featured h2 { font-size: var(--text-xl); color: var(--color-text); margin-bottom: var(--space-3); }
  .cs-featured p { font-size: var(--text-sm); color: var(--color-muted); line-height: var(--leading-relaxed); margin-bottom: var(--space-5); }
  .cs-featured-stats { display: flex; gap: var(--space-6); margin-bottom: var(--space-4); }
  .cs-stat { display: flex; flex-direction: column; }
  .cs-stat-num { font-family: var(--font-heading); font-size: var(--text-xl); color: var(--color-text); font-weight: var(--weight-bold); line-height: 1; }
  .cs-stat-label { font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: var(--text-xs); color: var(--color-muted); margin-top: var(--space-1); }
  .cs-featured-stack { font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: var(--text-xs); color: var(--color-muted); opacity: 0.5; }

  /* Grid cards */
  .cs-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr); gap: var(--space-4); }
  .cs-card {
    background: var(--color-surface); border-radius: var(--radius-md); padding: var(--space-6);
    border: var(--border-width) solid color-mix(in srgb, var(--color-muted) 12%, transparent);
    position: relative;
  }
  .cs-card-number { font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: var(--text-xs); color: var(--color-primary); opacity: 0.4; margin-bottom: var(--space-3); }
  .cs-card h3 { font-size: var(--text-base); color: var(--color-text); margin-bottom: var(--space-2); }
  .cs-card p { font-size: var(--text-sm); color: var(--color-muted); line-height: var(--leading-normal); margin-bottom: var(--space-4); }
  .cs-card-stats { display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: var(--space-3); margin-bottom: var(--space-3); }
  .cs-card-stats span { font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 10px; color: var(--color-primary); background: color-mix(in srgb, var(--color-primary) 8%, transparent); padding: 2px 8px; border-radius: 3px; }
  .cs-card-stack { font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: var(--text-xs); color: var(--color-muted); opacity: 0.4; }

  /* CTA */
  .cs-cta { text-align: center; padding: var(--space-8) 0; }
  .cs-cta p { font-size: var(--text-md); color: var(--color-muted); line-height: var(--leading-relaxed); margin-bottom: var(--space-4); }
  .cs-cta-link { font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: var(--text-sm); color: var(--color-command); }
  .cs-cta-link:hover { color: var(--color-primary); }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .cs-featured { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .cs-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .cs-featured-stats { gap: var(--space-4); }
  }
</style>
